ASSESSMENT

LINUX
Module2

#Question1

find . -type f -size +1M > output.txt
	Finds all files larger than 1 MB in the current directory and its subdirectories.
	Saves the list of these files into output.txt.

#Question2

sed 's/localhost/127.0.0.1/g' config.txt > updated_config.txt

	Replaces all occurrences of localhost with 127.0.0.1 in config.txt.
	Saves the updated content into updated_config.txt.

#Question3

grep "ERROR" log.txt | grep -v "DEBUG" > filtered_log.txt

	Searches for lines containing "ERROR" in log.txt.
	Excludes lines that also contain "DEBUG".
	Saves the filtered lines to filtered_log.txt.

#Question4

ps aux --sort=-%mem | awk 'NR==2 {print $1}' | xargs kill -9

	Lists all running processes with details like user, PID, CPU and memory usage, and command.
	awk 'NR==2 {print $1}'selects the PID of the process using the most memory.
	xargs passes this PID as an argument to kill -9.
	kill -9 forcefully terminates that process.
	xargs is used to take the output of one command and use it as input for another.

#Question5

awk 'NR>1 {print $2}' gateway


	Reads the file gateway.
	Skips the first line.
	Prints the second column of each remaining line.
